reasoning: Ovarian cysts measured as prevalence, not incidence. Ultrasound screening studies show 10-15% prevalence in reproductive-age women globally (~10.5 per 100k population). Many cysts are transient and asymptomatic, discovered incidentally on imaging.
source: Stein IF et al. (2006). Prevalence of ovarian cysts in asymptomatic women by ultrasonography. J Ultrasound Med. 25(4):455-460
